          <a class=3D"link back" href=3D"https://youthoncourse.org/yoc-blog=
">
            Back to all
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"post-entry">
          <div class=3D"post-header">
            <span class=3D"cat-link">
             =20
             =20
              <a class=3D"blog-post__tag-link" href=3D"https://youthoncours=
e.org/yoc-blog/tag/resources">Resources</a>
             =20
             =20
            </span>
            <h1 class=3D"post-title"><span id=3D"hs_cos_wrapper_name" class=
=3D"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_meta_field hs_cos_wrapper_type_text" styl=
e=3D"" data-hs-cos-general-type=3D"meta_field" data-hs-cos-type=3D"text">A =
Guide to Understanding Golf Handicaps</span></h1>
            <p class=3D"post-date">April 1, 2025 / by Youth on Course</p>
          </div>

          <div class=3D"post-content">
           =20
            <div class=3D"post-featured-image-wrapper pb-3">
             =20
             =20
             =20
            </div>
           =20
            <div class=3D"post-content__body">
              <span id=3D"hs_cos_wrapper_post_body" class=3D"hs_cos_wrapper=
 hs_cos_wrapper_meta_field hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text" style=3D"" data-h=
s-cos-general-type=3D"meta_field" data-hs-cos-type=3D"rich_text"><p data-pm=
-slice=3D"1 1 []"><span>At Youth on Course, our core values are rooted in r=
elationships, inclusion, play, and learning. Above all, we want our members=
 to have fun and enjoy their time on the course. Whether you=E2=80=99re out=
 for a relaxing round with friends or discovering your love for the game, Y=
outh on Course is here to make golf accessible and enjoyable.</span></p>
<!--more-->
<p><span>For those looking to measure your improvement, and compete, whethe=
r it=E2=80=99s a casual match with family and friends, or a tournaments, or=
 simply measure your improvement, establishing a <a href=3D"https://www.usg=
a.org/content/usga/home-page/get-handicap.html" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"=
_blank">Handicap Index<sup>=C2=AE</sup></a> is a great next step.<br></span=
><a href=3D"https://www.planetdivot.com/ghin-guide-to-golf-handicap" rel=3D=
"noopener" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: u=
nderline;"></a></p>
<p><span><span style=3D"font-weight: bold;">What Is the World Handicap Syst=
em (WHS)?</span><br>Introduced in 2020, the <a href=3D"https://www.whs.com/=
" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">World Handicap System (WHS)</a> provid=
es a unified way for golfers worldwide to calculate and maintain their hand=
icaps. The system ensures fairness by adjusting for course difficulty and a=
 player=E2=80=99s recent performance, making it easier for golfers to compe=
te anywhere, on any course.</span></p>
<p><span><img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://youthoncourse.org/hs-fs/hubfs=
/fun_132_youth_on_course_dundore_photo_20240603-2-1.jpg?width=3D1200&amp;he=
ight=3D800&amp;name=3Dfun_132_youth_on_course_dundore_photo_20240603-2-1.jp=
g" width=3D"1200" height=3D"800" alt=3D"fun_132_youth_on_course_dundore_pho=
to_20240603-2-1" style=3D"height: auto; max-width: 100%; width: 1200px;"><b=
r><br><span style=3D"font-weight: bold;">Key features of the WHS include:</=
span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span><strong>A Handicap Index<sup>=C2=AE</sup></strong> =E2=80=93 A nu=
mber that represents your potential ability (e.g., 12.4).</span></li>
<li><span><strong>Course &amp; Slope Ratings</strong> =E2=80=93 Adjusts you=
r handicap based on the difficulty of the course you=E2=80=99re playing.</s=
pan></li>
<li><span><strong>Net Double Bogey Limit</strong> =E2=80=93 Prevents one ba=
d hole from drastically affecting your score.</span></li>
<li><span><strong>Playing Conditions Calculation (PCC)</strong> =E2=80=93 A=
djusts scores if weather or course conditions are unusually tough.</span></=
li>
</ul>
<span><span style=3D"font-weight: bold;">Reasons to get a Handicap:<br></sp=
an></span><br>
<ul>
<li><span><strong>Track Progress</strong> =E2=80=93 See how your game impro=
ves over time.</span></li>
<li><span><strong>Compete Fairly</strong> =E2=80=93 Play in tournaments or =
matches against friends, regardless of skill level.</span></li>
<li><span><strong>Set Goals</strong> =E2=80=93 Use your handicap as a bench=
mark to challenge yourself.</span></li>
<li><span><strong>Access More Golf Opportunities</strong> =E2=80=93 Some ev=
ents and leagues require an official handicap.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span><img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://youthoncourse.org/hs-fs/hubfs=
/Youth%20on%20Course%20App%20Post%20Scores.png?width=3D1500&amp;height=3D10=
00&amp;name=3DYouth%20on%20Course%20App%20Post%20Scores.png" width=3D"1500"=
 height=3D"1000" alt=3D"Youth on Course App Post Scores" style=3D"height: a=
uto; max-width: 100%; width: 1500px;"></span></p>
<p><span><strong>How to Post Scores via the Youth on Course app:</strong></=
span></p>
<ul>
<li><span><strong>Log in</strong> - Download the <a href=3D"https://onelink=
.to/youthoncourse" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"font-weight:=
 bold; text-decoration: underline;">Youth on Course mobile app</a> and log =
in</span></li>
<li><span><strong>Post Your Scores</strong> =E2=80=93 After each round, nav=
igate to the Post Score section in the Youth on Course mobile app and enter=
 the course, tees you played, and score for your round. <em>*Note: Certain =
states do not provide GHIN with memberships so those members will not be ab=
le to post scores in the app.&nbsp;</em></span></li>
<li><strong>Play and Post 54 holes</strong> - 54 holes are required to esta=
blish a handicap. Your handicap will be No handicap (NH) until 54 holes are=
 reached.</li>
<li><span><strong>Watch Your Handicap Update</strong> =E2=80=93 Your Handic=
ap Index<sup>=C2=AE</sup> recalculates daily, based on your most recent 20 =
scores.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span><span style=3D"font-weight: bold;">Tips for Maintaining Your Handi=
cap:</span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span><strong>Post</strong> every eligible round</span></li>
<li><span><span style=3D"font-weight: bold;">Play</span> by the <a href=3D"=
https://www.usga.org/content/usga/home-page/rules-hub.html" rel=3D"noopener=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;=
">Rules of Golf</a> for accurate scoring.</span></li>
<li><span><strong>Keep an eye on your progress</strong>=E2=80=94improving y=
our handicap means improving your game!</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span><strong>Ready to Get Started?</strong><br>Your Youth on Course mem=
bership makes it easy to establish and track your handicap=E2=80=94so take =
advantage of this great resource! Whether you=E2=80=99re playing for fun or=
 aiming to compete, a Handicap Index=C2=AE helps you measure your growth an=
d enjoy the game even more.<br><br>Have questions or want to dive deeper an=
d learn more? Here are some additional resources:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://www.usga.org/content/usga/home-page/handicapping.htm=
l" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"font-weight: bold; text-deco=
ration: underline;">USGA Handicapping</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://www.randa.org/en/handicapping" rel=3D"noopener" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">The =
R&amp;A Handicapping</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://www.golfpass.com/travel-advisor/articles/golfs-handi=
cap-system-a-beginners-guide" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"f=
ont-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">GolfPass - How Does a Golf H=
andicap Work?: A Beginner=E2=80=99s Guide</a></li>
<li><span><a href=3D"https://www.usga.org/content/dam/usga/pdf/Handicap/10%=
20Things%20to%20Know%20Handicap%20Index%20-%20updated%20for%2024.pdf" rel=
=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"font-weight: bold; text-decoration=
: underline;">10 Things for Golfers to Know</a><br></span></li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"555" data-end=3D"1211"><span style=3D"font-weight: normal;=
">While having a GHIN handicap is not required to access Youth on Course be=
nefits, it can be a valuable tool for tracking improvement, playing fair ma=
tches, and participating in competitive tournaments.&nbsp;Course rating and=
 slope rating help adjust handicaps based on course difficulty, ensuring a =
fair assessment of a player=E2=80=99s skill.</span></p>
<p data-start=3D"1213" data-end=3D"1524" data-is-last-node=3D"" data-is-onl=
y-node=3D""><span style=3D"font-weight: normal;">For golfers looking to mea=
sure their progress or compete at a higher level, maintaining a handicap is=
 a great way to stay motivated and engaged in the game.</span></p></span>
